SIMPLE: twinge
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twinge
<hw>Twinge</hw> <pr>(tw⟦icr⟧nj)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Twinged</conjf>
<pr>(tw⟦icr⟧njd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Twinging</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>twengen</ets>, AS.
<ets>twengan</ets>; akin to OE. <ets>twingen</ets> to pain, afflict,
OFries. <ets>thwinga</ets>, <ets>twinga</ets>, <ets>dwinga</ets>, to
constrain, D. <ets>dwingen</ets>, OS. <ets>thwingan</ets>, G.
<ets>zwingen</ets>, OHG. <ets>dwingan</ets>, <ets>thwingan</ets>, to
press, oppress, overcome, Icel. <ets>⟦thorn⟧vinga</ets>, Sw.
<ets>tvinga</ets> to subdue, constrain, Dan. <ets>tvinge</ets>, and AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧⟦uum⟧n</ets> to press, OHG. <ets>d⟦umac⟧hen</ets>, and
probably to E. <ets>thong</ets>. Perhaps influenced by
<ets>twitch</ets>. Cf. <er>Thong</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pull
with a twitch; to pinch; to tweak.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When a man is past his sense,⟦br⟧
There's no way to reduce him thence,⟦br⟧
But <qex>twinging</qex> him by the ears or nose,⟦br⟧
Or laying on of heavy blows.</q> <rj><qau>Hudibras.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To affect with a sharp, sudden pain; to torment with
pinching or sharp pains.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The gnat . . . <qex>twinged</qex> him [the lion] till he made him
tear⟦br⟧
himself, and so mastered him.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twinge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twinge
<hw>Twinge</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To have a sudden, sharp, local
pain, like a twitch; to suffer a keen, darting, or shooting pain;
<as>as, the side <ex>twinges</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twinge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Twinge
<hw>Twinge</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A pinch; a tweak; a
twitch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A master that gives you . . . <qex>twinges</qex> by the ears.</q>
<rj><qau>L' Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sudden sharp pain; a darting local pain of
momentary continuance; <as>as, a <ex>twinge</ex> in the arm or
side</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ A <xex>twinge</xex> for my own sin.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twining</ent>⟦br⟧
